# NestJS Service Rules

## Structure

Each NestJS service follows this structure:
```
services/<name>-service/
├── src/
│   ├── main.ts
│   ├── app.module.ts
│   ├── <domain>/
│   │   ├── <domain>.module.ts
│   │   ├── <domain>.controller.ts
│   │   ├── <domain>.service.ts
│   │   ├── dto/
│   │   │   ├── create-<domain>.dto.ts
│   │   │   └── update-<domain>.dto.ts
│   │   └── entities/
│   │       └── <domain>.entity.ts
│   └── common/
│       ├── guards/
│       ├── interceptors/
│       └── filters/
├── prisma/
│   └── schema.prisma
├── tests/
│   ├── unit/
│   └── integration/
├── package.json
├── tsconfig.json
└── Dockerfile
```

## Database

- Use Prisma ORM for all database operations
- Schema defined in `prisma/schema.prisma`
- Run `npx prisma migrate dev` for schema changes
- Always use transactions for multi-table operations

## API Response Format

Success: `{ data: T, meta?: { page, limit, total } }`
Error: `{ error: { code: string, message: string, message_key: string, trace_id: string } }`

## Testing

- Unit tests in `tests/unit/` for services and business logic
- Integration tests in `tests/integration/` for controllers and API
- Use `jest` with `@nestjs/testing`
- Mock external dependencies (database, message queue)
